relation: The campus has a lot of things in place to ensure safety. They have a safe walk program where you will get a police escort if you are afraid to walk alone at night. Also they have emergency buttons located all over campus where you can recieve help immediatly after pushing one of them.
There are so many clubs and activities on campus. Every semester they have a fair where you can learn about the clubs and get involved which is really awesome.
You get a great education for the tuition you pay.
Uw-Oshkosh has a great rec center and is also on the river so there are many fun outdoor activities.
There are a multiple dining area's on campus that include a variety of different types of food. Blackhawk offers an all you can eat buffet which is pretty good.
The dorm environment is very comfortable and fun. In the dorms they have community advisors who help make the dorm life more enjoyable and fun.
The course work is chanllenging, but the professors are always willing to help if you are struggling.
Get involved right away, there are a lot of clubs and activities on campus that are really great.

The University of Wisconsin-Oshkosh campus is a very beautiful and friendly campus. The staff and student on campus are very helpful and the services offered are tremendous. The University of Wisconsin-Oshkosh has a lot to offer to everyone.

textAfterTable: Tips for prospective students I would recommend to every student to get involved in the student government. It is a flawless way to meet new people, have fun, and help the university. It is also extremely important to be aware of your own needs and attend to them. If you are having any troubles with your roommate, your floor, or even a friend, talk to someone. Never be afraid to reach out to your Campus Advisor, academic advisor, or the professional advisors located on campus. They will always help you to fix a situation. Bang for the buck UW Oshkosh is such an exciting school to attend. There are always community events occurring and so many diverse ways to get involved and meet new people. The residence halls are also very well kept and safe. There are many measures taken to ensure the safety and integrity of the residents, such as locked resident halls to anyone without a key card, and bathroom keys for every floor. Every night there are guards at each entrance to ensure the protection of students, as well. The university itself offers a wide variety of majors, minors, and general education classes for anyone to enroll. The classes are very educational, and always appropriately challenging.
